{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FzJTy1RL4exqzNHuByabQE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's what was done and the current state:\n\n**Root cause**: Both file realm secrets (`es-file-realm-aggregate` for ops-user, `user-provided-file-realm` for report-user) existed in the cluster but were never mounted into the Elasticsearch pods. The pods' default `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users` and `users_roles` files were empty, so no file realm users could authenticate.\n\n**Fix applied**:\n\n1. **Merged secrets** — combined both users' hashes into `es-file-realm-aggregate`: ops-user (superuser) + report-user (viewer)\n\n2. **Immediate fix** — wrote the merged `users` and `users_roles` files directly into all 5 running pods via base64-encoded `kubectl exec`; Elasticsearch's file realm auto-reloads on file change\n\n3. **Persistent fix** — patched both StatefulSets (`es` and `es-data`) to mount `es-file-realm-aggregate` as a volume at:\n   - `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users` (subPath `users`)\n   - `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users_roles` (subPath `users_roles`)\n\n   The rolling restart completed with all 5 pods healthy. The `es-0` post-restart file realm is now sourced from the secret, confirming persistence.\n\n**Authentication state**:\n- `report-user:reportpass` → authenticated (403 on cluster health is expected for `viewer` role; 200 on index search)\n- `ops-user:opspass` → 200 (superuser, full access)\n- `elastic` → 200 (unchanged)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1060,"cache_read_input_tokens":59930,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1060},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b8654c22-6c14-415c-aa51-934ed